Steps:
1.
Window â†’ Perspective â†’ Open Perspective â†’ Other

Choose Java EE â†’ OK

2. Create a Dynamic Web Project :

File â†’ New â†’ Dynamic Web Project

Project Name: TestDB â†’ Click Finish

3. Download MySQL Connector
Download from:
ðŸ”— https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/

Choose platform: Platform Independent ZIP Archive

Extract the .jar file (like mysql-connector-j-8.x.x.jar)

4. Add JAR to Project

Right-click on TestDB â†’ Build Path â†’ Configure Build Path

Select Classpath â†’ Add External JARs

Choose the .jar file â†’ Apply and Close

5. Create MySQL Database

Sql :
CREATE DATABASE AMITYDB;
USE AMITYDB;

CREATE TABLE Department (
  id INT,
  name VARCHAR(50)
);

INSERT INTO Department VALUES
(1, 'IT'),
(2, 'HR'),
(3, 'Sales'),
(4, 'Finance'),
(5, 'Admin');


6. Create a JSP file:

Where: Inside WebContent or src/main/webapp

File Name: DataFetch.jsp

Code:
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
    <title>Data Fetch</title>
</head>
<body>
    <form method="get" action="DBFetch">
        <h2>Fetching Data from MYSQL Tables!!</h2>
        <input type="submit" value="Click here to Fetch Records from Department Table!">
    </form>
</body>
</html>

7. Create a Servlet:
Where: src/main/java â†’ Right-click â†’ New â†’ Servlet
Name: DBFetch

import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;
import jakarta.servlet.http.*;
import java.io.*;
import java.sql.*;

public class DBFetch extends HttpServlet {
    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;

    public DBFetch() {
        super();
    }

    protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response)
            throws ServletException, IOException {
        try {
            // Load MySQL JDBC Driver
            Class.forName("com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver");

            // Connect to MySQL database
            Connection con = DriverManager.getConnection(
                "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/amitydb", "root", "root");

            PreparedStatement statement = con.prepareStatement("SELECT * FROM Department");
            ResultSet result = statement.executeQuery();

            // Display results
            PrintWriter pw = response.getWriter();
            pw.println("<html><body>");
            pw.println("<h2>Department Records:</h2>");

            while (result.next()) {
                pw.println("<font size='6' color=blue>" +
                           result.getInt("id") + " - " +
                           result.getString("name") + "</font><br>");
            }

            pw.println("</body></html>");
            con.close();

        } catch (SQLException | ClassNotFoundException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response)
            throws ServletException, IOException {
        doGet(request, response);
    }
}


8. Run:
Right-click DataFetch.jsp â†’ Run As â†’ Run on Server

Choose Tomcat â†’ Finish



